author: Warhammer
description:
Yep, it’s that time of year again! Grotmas is just around the corner and with it comes a brand new festive miniature. Marching through the snow is Da Red Gobbo’s Tinboy! In this beginner-friendly video, Ollie shows you how to build and paint this awesome mini, using only 10 paints!

Here’s a list of the paints we used in today’s video:

Base:
Corax White
Leadbelcher
Steel Legion Drab

Contrast:
Apothecary White
Asurmen Blue
Bad Moon Yellow
Blood Angels Red
Striking Scorpion Green

Layer:
Canoptek Alloy

Shade:
Agrax Earthshade

Brushes:
Large Base
Small Base
Small Layer
Small Dry
Medium Shade

If you enjoyed this and want to learn more, our YouTube channel has an array of beginner-friendly videos to get you started.
